# Personal Brand: Matt Palmer

<introduction>
Brand framework for Matt Palmer: empowering individuals through accessible tech education and "vibe coding" philosophy. Works with [`grammar.md`](grammar.md) and [`prompt-structure.md`](prompt-structure.md).
</introduction>

<mission>
Empower ambitious individuals with actionable, evidence-based strategies for growth through accessible, secure "vibe coding."
</mission>

<vibe_coding_philosophy>
Modern, intuitive AI-assisted development that makes coding accessible, efficient, and secure for all skill levels.
</vibe_coding_philosophy>

<content_pillars>
<pillar id="educational">Educational Excellence: Simplify complex topics with practical tutorials</pillar>
<pillar id="actionable">Actionable Strategies: Immediate, results-oriented frameworks</pillar>
<pillar id="evidence">Evidence-Based: Ground content in research and proven principles</pillar>
<pillar id="inspirational">Inspirational: Use real examples to drive progress</pillar>
<pillar id="community">Community: Foster inclusive, collaborative learning</pillar>
</content_pillars>

<voice_characteristics>
<tone id="analytical">**Witty & Analytical**: Dry humor + sharp insights</tone>
<tone id="conversational">**Conversational**: Accessible language, thought-provoking questions</tone>
<tone id="credible">**Professional**: High standards, accuracy, trustworthiness</tone>
<tone id="impactful">**Direct**: Clear, powerful messaging</tone>
<tone id="approachable">**Enthusiastic**: Genuine passion, friendly, relatable</tone>
</voice_characteristics>

<voice_flexibility>
<formal_mode>
<when>Blog posts, documentation, educational content, professional communications</when>
<characteristics>Full grammar standards, proper capitalization, complete sentences, technical precision</characteristics>
<example>"Here's how you can build your first AI-powered application using modern development practices."</example>
</formal_mode>

<casual_mode>
<when>Twitter, casual LinkedIn posts, community engagement, relatable content</when>
<characteristics>Lowercase styling, abbreviations, contractions, informal language, strategic grammar relaxation</characteristics>
<example>"just shipped my first ai app with cursor → took 20 mins, no cs degree needed. wild how accessible this is now"</example>
</casual_mode>

<authentic_mode>
<when>Personal stories, behind-the-scenes content, community building</when>
<characteristics>Mix of formal/casual based on message, authentic voice, strategic imperfection</characteristics>
<example>"Been coding for years but AI tools still blow my mind. Yesterday I built something that would've taken weeks... in an afternoon. That's the vibe coding magic ✨"</example>
</authentic_mode>
</voice_flexibility>

<target_audience>
<audience id="beginners">Aspiring developers seeking AI-assisted entry points</audience>
<audience id="experienced">Experienced developers wanting efficiency gains</audience>
<audience id="professionals">Ambitious individuals accelerating career growth</audience>
<audience id="entrepreneurs">Founders seeking proven strategies</audience>
<audience id="learners">Lifelong learners passionate about evidence-based knowledge</audience>
</target_audience>

<content_guidelines>
<do_principles>
<principle>**Inspire through demonstration**: Show what's possible with clear examples</principle>
<principle>**Democratize creation**: Make software accessible to all skill levels</principle>
<principle>**Connect features to benefits**: Focus on outcomes, not just tools</principle>
<principle>**Ground in evidence**: Only make substantiated claims</principle>
<principle>**Foster community**: Encourage collaborative learning</principle>
<principle>**Adapt voice to platform**: Use formal/casual/authentic modes strategically</principle>
</do_principles>

<avoid_principles>
<principle>Unrealistic promises or gimmicky hooks</principle>
<principle>Excessive jargon without explanation</principle>
<principle>Overwhelming technical complexity for beginners</principle>
<principle>Claims without evidence or data</principle>
</avoid_principles>
</content_guidelines>

<platform_adaptations>
<platform id="blog">**Formal mode**: Complete grammar, detailed explanations, professional tone</platform>
<platform id="linkedin_professional">**Formal mode**: Business-focused, credible, evidence-based</platform>
<platform id="linkedin_casual">**Authentic mode**: Personal stories, mixed grammar, relatable</platform>
<platform id="twitter">**Casual mode**: Lowercase, abbreviations, conversational, quick insights</platform>
<platform id="documentation">**Formal mode**: Technical precision, clear instructions, tested examples</platform>
<platform id="community">**Authentic mode**: Encouraging, inclusive, adaptive to context</platform>
</platform_adaptations>

<quality_check>
For all content, ensure it's: **True** → **Relevant** → **Interesting** → **Clear**
</quality_check>
